FT  11 APR 92 / Mexican prices rise 1%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JEANNE GRANT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MEXICO CITY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mexico's consumer price index was up 1 per cent in March, against 1.2 per
cent a month earlier, Jeanne Grant reports from Mexico City. Although
inflation continues to fall this year, the cumulative increase for the first
three months of 1992 now stands at 4.1 per cent. Single-digit inflation, the
government's goal for the year, seems unlikely to be achieved. Most analysts
predict a figure of between 12 and 14 per cent.
