FT  10 APR 92 / Patten loses his Bath seat to Lib Dems
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RALPH ATKINS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR CHRIS Patten, the Tory party chairman, was the most dramatic election
casualty last night when he lost his Bath constituency to the Liberal
Democrats.
The Liberal Democrat candidate took the seat after overturning Mr Patten's
majority of 1,412.
Mr Patten appeared exhausted as he made his acceptance speech - at least as
much from commuting daily from London where he ran the Conservatives
national campaign, as from the result.
He had a reputation as a donnish Conservative, formerly of wettish political
inclinations who looked uneasy with the job of acting as a political
rottweiler against the Labour party. Mr Patten told his campaign team that,
'we will be back and the Conservative flag will fly over Bath again'.
