FT  10 APR 92 / UK Company News: Receivers in at Isis Group
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Robert Birchall of the Bristol office of Cork Gully has been appointed
administrative receiver to Isis Group.
The main trading company within the group is Isis Construction, which
specialises in commercial and industrial building work. It has a turnover of
some Pounds 30m and employs about 120 staff.
The other two companies are relatively small; Wessex Guild, a maker of
architectural metalwork, with turnover of Pounds 3m employing 25 staff and
Isis Pneumatics, which has turnover of Pounds 4m and about 50 employees.
Mr Birchall said the group had been in difficulties for some time. There had
been negotiations with companies interested in the business but these had
not been concluded.
Shares in Isis, an over-the counter stock, were last dealt in June 1991 at
40p through Granville Securities.
