FT  10 APR 92 / Letter: Political stance seen as 'breaking rule' and a
disservice - but supported by example
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr JOE BANERJEE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, A word of thanks to the FT for following your heads and advising
readers to vote Labour. We here in Japan are all too aware what happens to a
political system that gets used to one-party rule.
Joe Banerjee,
402 Maison Fonteyn,
830-6 Bomoncho,
Shimogyo-ku, Kyoto,
Japan
