<BYLINE>
   By VANESSA HOULDER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ST JOHNS Hospital, near Leicester Square in central London, has been sold
for redevelopment to a Chinese buyer for almost Pounds 3m, Vanessa Houlder
writes.
The sale, by South East Thames Regional Health Authority, reflects the
health service's efforts to rationalise its estate.
The buyer is considering asking for planning permission for restaurants, a
community centre, housing and a private hospital. Existing planning
permission for offices is unlikely to be acted on. The facade is listed and
will be kept.
Allsop, the agent which conducted the sale, said the building had attracted
strong interest, particularly from Hong Kong.
