<HEADLINE>
FT  09 APR 92 / International Company News: Canal Plus has 18.8% gain -
lifts dividend
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By Agencies
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   Paris
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CANAL PLUS, Europe's leading pay-television station, increased its 1991
consolidated net attributable profit by 18.8 per cent to FFr1.08bn (Dollars
190m) from FFr910m a year earlier, agencies report from Paris.
Operating profit increased to FFr1.91bn from FFr1.66bn. The figures allow
for a loss from affiliated companies of FFr354m against a loss of FFr194m in
1990.
Turnover amounted to FFr7bn, up from FFr6.13bn.
The net profit figure was in line with the company's own estimate. Earnings
per share rose by 16.9 per cent to FFr58.7 from FFr50.2 and Canal Plus said
it intends to raise its net dividend to FFr23 a share from FFr20.
Canal Plus said the strong rise in net profit last year occurred despite
provisions of FFr115.5m for TV South, a UK TV station in which the French
company has a 12 per cent stake, and for Carolco, a US film production
company in which a Canal Plus unit has a 10 per cent interest.
Last year's earnings were also affected by Canal Plus's share of the cost of
new ventures, which almost doubled to FFr290m from FFr150.2m.
Looking ahead, Canal Plus said it expects to maintain its growth momentum in
France, while subsidiaries are expected to grow at an even faster pace,
especially outside France.
</TEXT>
