<HEADLINE>
FT  09 APR 92 / Capital expenditure by chemical industry
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CAPITAL expenditure by the chemical industry fell 13 per cent in 1991 and
will fall a further 10 per cent this year.
The 1992 fall, predicted today by the Chemical Industry Association, is in
spite of record sums being spent by the chemicals sector on environmental
protection, and substantial amounts invested by the pharmaceuticals groups
on research and development.
The association warned that 1992 was going to be another tough year for the
UK's chemical industry. Since January, little had happened to improve
prospects of an economic recovery either internationally or domestically, it
said.
Moreover, high levels of debt, shortage of capital and the likelihood of
continuing high levels of interest rates would mean that the projected
recovery would be much slower than that after the recession between 1980 and
1981.
</TEXT>
